Now you're just making up excuses.  They don't flicker because...<br /><br />1)  it's easier to program a video emulation driver that doesn't emulate the PPU to the point of artifacts such as that, &amp;...<br />2)  Nintendo is ALOT bigger, which means more flickering = more seizure lawsuits.  That's why you get the warning message whenever you power on any modern Nintendo console.  They've even gone through the trouble of modifying virtual consoler ROMS to reduce the amount of flickering.  That's why you don't get the classic red, green, blue death animation in Zelda II.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3367">atari2600a</a> — Thu Sep 06, 2007 4:17 pm</p><hr />
